                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8508: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-02T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 2, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>112. Your 261, October 1, 4 p.m. It will be understood, I feel sure, that
                    following our policy of noninterference and nonintervention we would prefer not
                    to have American officers engaged in the work of this commission.</p>
                <p>Please therefore discourage the idea of appointing an American officer on the
                    League Commission for the Evacuation of Foreign Volunteers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
